      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i had a small cyst removed by my doctor a few days ago here in sydney and the cut is looking a bit weird. its kind of red and feels warm to the touch, and there is a bit of this yellowish fluid oozing out of it. is that normal or should i be worried? i dont really want to go back to the clinic if i dont have to",
