      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While a warm compress can be helpful for promoting healing, not everyone's reaction to minor procedures is the same, and some symptoms, like the yellowish fluid, can sometimes indicate a persistent infection or other issues. Applying Neosporin to the wound may not be enough to address potential infection, and over-the-counter ointments don't replace professional evaluation and guidance. I would still advise you to schedule a follow-up appointment with your doctor to have your wound assessed and cleared.",
